article.headline: New Orleans 77, Fla. International 67
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored a game-high 27 points and sparked a huge second-half run as New Orleans defeated Florida International 77-67 in a Sun Belt Conference game on Thursday. McCalebb scored 18 points in the second half, including eight during a 17-2 run as UNO (10-11, 6-4 Sun Belt) won its first league home game since Dec. 16. Asrangue Souleymane, making just his second start of the year, had a season-high 14 points and 12 rebounds, while James Parlow added 13 points. Souleymane also had five blocked shots. Alex Galindo led FIU (8-12, 3-7 Sun Belt) with 18 points. The Golden Panthers had just eight players available due to various injuries and all eight saw action. UNO led by as many as nine with 7:38 left in the first half but only led 34-33 at halftime. The two teams went back and forth to start the second half, and Nikola Gacesa buried a 3-pointer with 13:26 left to give FIU a 46-45 lead. The Privateers, though, held FIU to 1-for-7 from the field during the next five minutes while McCalebb and Souleymane combined for 12 points to help grab a 62-48 advantage. New Orleans never led by less than nine the rest of the way.
